Digital Identity Credential Network L1
Overview

Digital Identity Credential Network L1 provides infrastructure for issuing, verifying, and managing digital identity credentials.

Features

Verifiable credentials

Identity authentication

Secure credential storage

Interoperable identity standards

Privacy-preserving verification

Architecture
Credential Issuance Layer

Creates digital identity certificates.

Identity Wallet Integration

Stores user credentials.

Verification Engine

Validates identity claims.

Privacy Layer

Protects sensitive information.

Use Cases

Digital passports

Educational certificates

KYC verification

Employment verification
